# Constructor — environment template.
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. NEVER commit the real .env.

# CONSTRUCTOR_PII_KEY — AES-256-GCM key for buyer_identity PII at rest (Article IV).
# Exactly 32 bytes, encoded as base64 (44 chars) or hex (64 chars).
# Generate one:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
# If the key is missing or malformed, the PII path refuses to run (fail-secure).
# Losing the key makes existing encrypted PII unrecoverable — back it up in the
# agency's password manager. Erasure (eraseIdentity) works even without the key.
CONSTRUCTOR_PII_KEY=
